        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add harness-aware run evidence",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Adds harness-aware evidence for `crabbox run` and `crabbox job run`: Markdown harness parsing, YAML frontmatter validation, plan/harness hashes, light grounding metadata, and local compliance reports.\n- Adds `crabbox harness validate [--json] HARNESS.md` plus job config support for `harness.path` / `harness.index` defaults in `.crabbox.yaml`.\n- Documents harness usage, evidence outputs, compliance behavior, and a generic Harness/Station/Reasoning Station roadmap.\n- After merging latest `main`, this PR no longer includes root OpenClaw plugin tool additions; those can be reconsidered separately because main removed the root plugin package.\n\n## What The New Pieces Do\n- `internal/cli/harness.go`: parses harness Markdown/frontmatter, rejects unknown top-level and nested frontmatter keys, computes hashes, builds grounding JSON, writes remote/local evidence, and renders compliance reports.\n- `run` / `job run`: accept `--harness` and `--index none|light`; harness metadata is included in timing JSON and compliance failures can make an otherwise successful command return nonzero.\n- Delegated providers such as Islo emit the final harness-aware timing report from the CLI when a harness is attached.\n- Compliance reports write `harness.md`, `grounding.json`, `compliance-report.md`, and `compliance-report.json` under `.crabbox/runs/<run-or-lease>/`.\n\n## Review Fixes Included\n- Fixed CLI flag examples/order so `--json` and `job run --harness` match the Go parsers.\n- Fixed required artifact compliance so unrelated artifacts no longer satisfy all requirements, and JUnit evidence can satisfy `required_artifacts: junit` when results were parsed.\n- Fixed compliance ordering so proof artifacts are produced before harness compliance is evaluated, allowing proof evidence to be required.\n- Fixed delegated-run harness compliance so delegated execution errors cannot look like a passed harness because of a zero-valued result exit code.\n- Fixed harness compliance finalization so a command that exits 0 but fails compliance is recorded in run history and timing JSON with the effective harness failure exit code.\n- Fixed delegated-provider timing so Islo-style harness runs emit a single final harness-aware timing JSON report from the CLI.\n- Simplified job-level `harness:` config to only `path` and `index`, the values that `job run` can forward to the nested `run`; plan/scope/compliance live in the harness file.\n- Added safety boundaries: harness `plan_file` values must be safe repo-relative paths before Crabbox reads/hashes them.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal CI-equivalent verification after merging latest `main`:\n\n```text\n$ gofmt -l $(git ls-files '*.go')\n# no output\n\n$ go vet ./... && go test -race ./...\nok  \tgithub.com/openclaw/crabbox/cmd/crabbox\t2.153s\nok  \tgithub.com/openclaw/crabbox/internal/cli\t56.046s\n...\nok  \tgithub.com/openclaw/crabbox/internal/providers/wandb\t11.777s\n\n$ node --test scripts/*.test.js\nℹ tests 51\nℹ pass 51\nℹ fail 0\n\n$ scripts/check-docs.sh\nchecked 42 command docs: command surface ok\nchecked 139 markdown files: internal links ok\nbuilt docs site: dist/docs-site\n\n$ npm ci && npm run format:check && npm run lint && npm run check && npm test && npm run build  # in worker/\nAll matched files use the correct format.\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\nTest Files 14 passed (14)\nTests 316 passed (316)\nwrangler deploy --dry-run completed successfully.\n```\n\n## Real Islo Runtime Proof\n\nI used the installed `islo` CLI to create a temporary API key, ran two real `crabbox run --provider islo --harness ... --timing-json` invocations against a tiny throwaway git repo, then removed the local key file and deactivated/deleted the generated key. Sandbox ids, friendly slugs, and local temp paths are redacted below.\n\nPassing harness run:\n\n```text\n$ crabbox run --provider islo --islo-image docker.io/library/ubuntu:26.04 \\\n  --harness HARNESS-pass.md --timing-json --label pr190-islo-pass -- \\\n  /bin/sh -c 'printf \"islo harness pass\\\\n\"'\n\nstdout:\nislo harness pass\n\nstderr excerpt:\nleased isb_<redacted> slug=<redacted> provider=islo sandbox=<redacted>\nprovider=islo lease=isb_<redacted> sandbox=<redacted>\nsync candidate: 4 files, 296 B\nsync complete in 1.08s\nislo run summary sync=1.08s command=478ms total=56.507s exit=0\nartifact kind=harness path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/harness.md bytes=131\nartifact kind=grounding path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/grounding.json bytes=642\nartifact kind=compliance-json path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/compliance-report.json bytes=413\nartifact kind=compliance-report path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/compliance-report.md bytes=256\n{\"provider\":\"islo\",\"syncDelegated\":true,\"exitCode\":0,\"label\":\"pr190-islo-pass\",\"harness\":{\"path\":\"HARNESS-pass.md\",\"template\":\"smoke\",\"planHash\":\"<redacted>\",\"index\":\"light\",\"status\":\"passed\"}}\n```\n\nCompliance-failing harness run (remote command exits 0, harness fails because required evidence is absent):\n\n```text\n$ crabbox run --provider islo --islo-image docker.io/library/ubuntu:26.04 \\\n  --harness HARNESS-fail.md --timing-json --label pr190-islo-fail -- \\\n  /bin/sh -c 'printf \"islo harness compliance fail\\\\n\"'\n\nstdout:\nislo harness compliance fail\n\nstderr excerpt:\nleased isb_<redacted> slug=<redacted> provider=islo sandbox=<redacted>\nprovider=islo lease=isb_<redacted> sandbox=<redacted>\nsync candidate: 4 files, 296 B\nsync complete in 1.179s\nislo run summary sync=1.179s command=438ms total=53.306s exit=0\nartifact kind=harness path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/harness.md bytes=144\nartifact kind=grounding path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/grounding.json bytes=619\nartifact kind=compliance-json path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/compliance-report.json bytes=404\nartifact kind=compliance-report path=<tmp>/.crabbox/runs/run/compliance-report.md bytes=231\n{\"provider\":\"islo\",\"syncDelegated\":true,\"exitCode\":8,\"label\":\"pr190-islo-fail\",\"blockedStage\":\"harness-compliance\",\"retryLikely\":\"unknown\",\"harness\":{\"path\":\"HARNESS-fail.md\",\"template\":\"smoke\",\"index\":\"light\",\"status\":\"failed\"}}\nharness compliance failed\n```\n\nEvidence files produced by the Islo run:\n\n```text\n.crabbox/runs/run/harness.md\n.crabbox/runs/run/grounding.json\n.crabbox/runs/run/compliance-report.md\n.crabbox/runs/run/compliance-report.json\n```\n\n## Notes\n- Harnesses deliberately do not add LLM judging, vector indexes, scenario databases, autonomous state machines, or a remote daemon.\n- Agent/plugin exposure should be revisited separately after the root plugin package removal on `main` settles.",
